    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1931-05-05T00:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1931-05-05T00:00:00-05:00" n="767"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d767">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">825.00/644: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Chile</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Norweb</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Santiago</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-05-05T00:00:00-05:00"
                            >May 5, 1931—midnight</date>.<lb/>[Received May 6—4:20 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>42. Feeling against the Government has become more noticeable during the last few
                    days following upon the recent salary cuts and increased taxes which, together
                    with some defection in the Army and Navy, is being capitalized by the old
                    Conservative Party. In view thereof the President today issued a proclamation in
                    the form of orders to the provincial governors referring to the public unrest
                    and warning that he would not hesitate to use the armed forces of the country to
                    maintain order. This threat of force, added to recent deportations and the
                    arrest this morning of several members of the family of ex-President Alessandri
                    and their sympathizers, has created much indignation. There have been no
                    disorders but tension exists and the city is patrolled by large numbers of armed
                    soldiers and police. These measures indicate the Government’s apprehension.
                    Absolute censorship has been placed on all outgoing news but foreign
                    correspondents have been given a statement by the Minister of Finance and
                    requested to transmit it as a personal interview with the President. The
                    statement is intended only for foreign consumption and attempts to convey the
                    idea that the situation is normal.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Norweb</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
